			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				To tank or not to tank.<BR>
<BR>
Personaly if I can tank, I do.  Why?  Well for one I'd like to have a semi decent 2h blunt skill for the days coming when my pet dies and the &quot;oh my gosh now I have to defend myself&quot; time comes along.  It will happen.  More so than you think.  So in order to raise your skills you have to use them.  Thats one reason.  Secondly if I tank I level faster.  I can share damage, conserve mana for the big battles and kill more per hunting session than a burn burn burn med forever repeat hunting session.  Also I think its important to learn how to use your mana wisely.  Blowing it all cause ya can just isn't smart if you ask me.  Later when your in a group and in a dungeon you'll need to better use your mana on beefing up your pet, fire shielding your grouped players and saving that last big burn for the RED monster that got pulled along with the five blue ones.  That's just me of course.  I tank for pets cause I like to, I'm sick in the head I guess but it's allowed me to level faster, increase my weapon skills and save my pets for continus hours of hunting enjoyment.  <BR>
<BR>
Altoidus, Xegony
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
