			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I agree.  Magician's rock!  Here's a few tidbits I've learned so far and would like to share.<BR>
<BR>
Goal: I have 18th lvl bard and I was struggling with learning new skills, he's not that smart.  I read all kinds of websites that talked about int effecting your skills and such, made sense so i set out to make a new character and dabble in magic as well.  I picked an Erudite Magician.  I wanted a good solo class, and I must say so far the Magician rocks in that catagory.<BR>
So keep in mind this is all coming from an Erudite Magician stand point.<BR>
<BR>
Leveling: 1-4<BR>
<BR>
I hate toxx forest, it's puke green fog really made it tough at first.  Sure theres nobody there, max players in the zone at any one time was maybe eight.  In the city maybe three.  In any case get to 4th lvl here.<BR>
<BR>
Leveling: 4-6<BR>
<BR>
Qeynos.  Perfect newbie heaven.  Guards near by, tons of critters to kill.  You can't beat it.  If you need some extra cash I reccomend the &quot;report&quot; quest at the Bard's guild.  Quick easy gold that just asks you to run around a bit in the city delivering reports.  <BR>
<BR>
Leveling: 6-10<BR>
<BR>
Misty Thicket.  Another great newbie zone, perfect due to its size.  A nice well laid out area, you could also go 1-10 here no problem as well.  I highly reccomend this area.  Also keep in mind that you may be the only magician in the zone.  No halfling mages out there.  This makes you unique to the area.  Sure you may of had a hard time selling those summoned daggers and food and such in Qeynos, but here in the Misty Thickety they could use that sorta thing and pay for it. <BR>
<BR>
Leveling: 11-12<BR>
<BR>
East Commons.  A bit crowded but still a good zone.  I leveled solely on asps for these two levels and I made off with some good loot too.  Asp's kick but and they'll take you down in a hurry if your pet dies, either with thier bite or thier poision.  On the plus side they drop the ever popular giant snake fang worth about 4g.  All those asps and fangs add up.  Look into it.<BR>
<BR>
Leveling 13-14<BR>
<BR>
Steamfont.  This zone is great because there's hardly anyone ever here.  Pick up that Ward Summon spell and go to town here.  Tons of great mobs to hunt, minos, elementals, drakes, skels etc.  Good fun.  You're also in Akanon's back yard.  This means yer close a wide variety magician spells that cannot be found else where.  <BR>
<BR>
That's it so far.  I'll keep you posted.  Enjoy the magician, we're a great class.  Tank for your pets and keep those skills up.  <BR>
<BR>
Altoidus, Xegony<BR>
<BR>
Another<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
