	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Just  few corrections, additions:<BR>
<BR>
1) With the recent changes to magician pets, they are the best in the game, period. End of story. Any necro who tells you otherwise is full of it.<BR>
<BR>
2) Pets do not gain 5-10 points per attack per spell rank, which would mean my 20th level pets would do something on the order of 50 points per hit. I wish. My 20th pets, the good ones, something like 20 per hit. BUT they hit fast, and sometimes can do a double hit, kick (for 8 points or so) and cast a spell in one round. It is not unheard of for a 20th level pet to do 50 points or so in rapid succession.<BR>
<BR>
3) Earths are the best combat eles, most hit points and they hit the hardest. They get hit a lot tho, so, they are basically floating punching bags. I use earths outside and airs (which are invisible most of the time) indoors to avoid trains. I have not used a fire since 12th level.<BR>
<BR>
4) Much has been made of Mages having less powerful dd spells than other casters, which is and is not true. Our spells (particularly the blades series) are very difficult to resist, i found. That is something that you have to take into accout when comparing classes. Mages don't get root,  it's true. But we get pets, which are a much more effective root in most cases anyway. I, at least, wouldn't trade.<BR>
<BR>
5) As for selling conjored items, there is a market, although not a well developed one. Most summoned stuff CAN be saved after logout if they are first put in a bag and then in the bank. When people realize this, i expect there will be a healthy market, say, among rangers for summoned arrows, humans wanting heastones, all classes wanted bandages. Right now, i can sell summoned weapons to people who want to hunt wisps. I get requests all the time for them.<BR>
<BR>
6) One of the most common misperceptions about mages is the experience issue re: pets. here's the bottom line right from the designers: Pets ONLY take exp in a group IF they get the killing blow. Period. Therefore, any group that tells you they don't want to group with a pet for this reason doesn't know what they are talking about.<BR>
<BR>
Good hunting!
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
